    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels. The single shortfall in Test conditions (achieved 2, required 3) is accepted given the well-defined, single-configuration loading scenario defined by ASTM F1717 and the strong quantitative agreement observed across all three independent modeling teams. Overall credibility is sufficient to support regulatory submission for the non-cannulated pedicle screw design.",
